        <a id="automation" class="anchor"></a>
        <h2>User Experience and Meshing Productivity Enhancements</h2>
        <p>
          Learn about the new user interface tools for view manipulation and command navigation as well as many other additions to help generate meshes more quickly and efficiently.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Achieve quick access to the views and commands you need with the View Manipulator and expanded right-click Context Menu.
          </li>
          <li>
            Learn about the new online user manual for in-depth descriptions, videos, and examples of Pointwiseâ€™s commands.
          </li>
          <li>
            Master a suite of new commands created to accelerate the modification of connectors as well as the syncing and grouping of their associated spacing constraints.
          </li>
          <li>
            See how to use new diagnostic functions to find problematic cells and mesh intersections.
          </li>
          <li>
            Gain experience with the new Build Blocks command to rapidly create farfield blocks based on existing topology.
          </li>
        </ul>


        <img data-src="2018/images/ugm-training-800x365.png"
        alt="Overset data is displayed on a Persistent Cut for the ESAV." class="img-fluid center-block" />
        <figcaption>
          A farfield block and T-Rex layers are shown generated off the full DrivAer model.
        </figcaption>

        <a id="high-order" class="anchor"></a>
        <h2>Advanced Tools for Viscous and High Order Meshing</h2>
        <p>
          Get hands-on experience with these new features:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Create high order volume meshes (up to 4th degree) for all supported cell types.
          </li>
          <li>
            Quick top-down creation of new grid topology with Draw Shapes.
          </li>
          <li>
            Choose how anisotropic T-Rex (anisotropic tetrahedral extrusion) cells transition to isotropy to reduce pyramid counts in T-Rex blocks.
          </li>
          <li>
            Automatically apply 2-D T-Rex to unstructured domains.
          </li>
          <li>
            Control the final isotropic height of T-Rex layers for smooth transitions in difficult concave regions.
          </li>
          <li>
            Growth profiles that enable the automatic creation of laminar, turbulent, or customized boundary layer meshes.
          </li>
          <li>
            Grid import plugin SDK and other I/O improvements.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <img data-src="images/ugm-training-800x393.png"
        alt="Overset data is displayed on a Persistent Cut for the ESAV." class="img-fluid center-block" />
        <figcaption>
          Overset data is displayed on a Persistent Cut for the ESAV.
        </figcaption>

        <a id="coordinates" class="anchor"></a>
        <h2>Local Coordinates, Instancing, and Top-Down Meshing</h2>
        <p>
          Learn how to create mesh topology quickly and how to manage multibody overset meshes easily in independent meshing frameworks with these techniques:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Top-down block creation, including the new voxel block type, using Build Blocks for rapid refinement grid generation.
          </li>
          <li>
            Manage complex overset meshes with Frameworks and associated tools.
          </li>
          <li>
            Use attachment points to easily transform frameworks with respect to each other.
          </li>
          <li>
            Adapt block volumes and boundaries based on sources and grid entities.
          </li>
          <li>
            Split unstructured blocks based on distance or layer number.
          </li>
          <li>
            Use curve sources to align surface domain cells in critical regions.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <a id="refinement" class="anchor"></a>
        <h2>Advanced Mesh Diagnostics and Refinement</h2>
        <p>
          Get up to speed on all of the new Examine capabilities intended to facilitate your interrogation and management of complex overset grids:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Monitor key diagnostics with the widely requested new Examine persistent cuts feature.
          </li>
          <li>
            Use the new Examine Filters to isolate diagnostic ranges and picking cut locations.
          </li>
          <li>
            Obtain extensive overset object data via the enhanced cell/point probe.
          </li>
          <li>
            Generate cloud sources to refine your overset blocks exactly where you need.
          </li>
          <li>
            Learn how Pointwise integrates with popular mesh assemblers.
          </li>
        </ul>

